reviews.review_text: Gorgeous Sound This run from Atlanta, albeit one year before my time of seeing live shows, was always a fond one for me. The Foolish Heart and Death Don't from a couple nights before,(4-2-91) is an all time favorite set from this year. I'm NOT one of those types to criticize anything "after a certain year" because every era is its own entity with plenty of pluses in my book (e.g. Jerry's motivation and fingers may have suffered in later years, but the rest of the band was better than ever).  Anyway, this is not a spectacular setlist but well played and crystal sound. Love the little Stir it Up jam going into Drums as well...

Stir It Up man! 20yo and just blissed out, grew up in ATL & saw all Omni shows from '88 until '95. Spring '91 was peak. Bruce for a year and half was amazing Dead. I wonder aloud to the redneck next to me 'hey that tunes familiar...' He gives me a gap-toothed grin and proclaims 'Stir It Up man!' Jerry would generally only get musically silly like this when he's having a ball. Hot show. (And of course the Eyes and the Dark Star from Greensboro a few nights before were the most amazing I ever witnessed).
